From 8259d70f7ffbff8780fd770ad95bc230af690e61 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miha Kralj <miha@mihakralj.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 02:48:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman/pcd: KeyGen public API stub (PR14b-prep)

Lay down the ASK2 v1.0 PR14b foundation without touching FMan silicon
yet.  This change is mechanical scaffolding only - every public entry
point returns -EOPNOTSUPP (or ERR_PTR thereof).  The real KGSE_*
register programming and scheme allocator land in PR14b-body as a
modern in-tree implementation against LS1046A RM sec 8.7.4-8.7.5.

What this commit does
---------------------
1. New include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h KG section: declares
   enum fman_pcd_kg_extract_from, struct fman_pcd_kg_extract_spec,
   struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme_params, and the four public entry
   points fman_pcd_kg_scheme_create / bind_port / attach_cc /
   scheme_destroy.  ABI is what ask.ko M5 will consume.

2. New drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c (~110 LOC):
   stub bodies that perform input validation (-EINVAL on bad args,
   port_id range check 1..10 per RM sec 8.4) and return -EOPNOTSUPP
   for the silicon path.  Opaque struct fman_pcd_kg_scheme is fully
   defined here so consumers see only the forward decl.  All four
   entry points are EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL because ask.ko (GPL, out-of-
   tree) is the sole consumer.

3. New drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen_internal.h:
   promotes the file-static struct keygen_scheme and struct
   fman_keygen from fman_keygen.c to module-internal scope, plus the
   FM_KG_MAX_NUM_OF_SCHEMES macro that dimensions the schemes[]
   array.  Header is fsl_dpaa_fman.ko-internal only; out-of-tree
   consumers go through the public surface.

4. fman_keygen.c: demote keygen_scheme_setup() and
   keygen_bind_port_to_schemes() from file-static to non-static
   and tag both EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL.  These are the existing in-tree
   helpers that already program the silicon for match_vector=0
   (RSS hashing); PR14b-body will reuse them after populating
   keygen->schemes[scheme_id] with match_vector != 0 for exact-
   match flow lookup.  Remove the two struct bodies that now live
   in the new header and #include the header in their place.

5. fman/Makefile: add fman_pcd_kg.o under CONFIG_FSL_FMAN_PCD so
   the stub links into fsl_dpaa_fman.ko exactly when PR14a's
   orchestration layer does.

Build verification (Cobalt 100 native arm64, gcc 13.3.0):
  make ARCH=arm64 -j32 Image
  -> zero warnings, zero errors
  System.map shows all six expected symbols (T) plus __ksymtab
  entries for the four EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL surfaces and the two
  EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL helpers promoted from fman_keygen.c.

No silicon registers are programmed by this commit.  Existing
fman_keygen.c behaviour (keygen_port_hashing_init() etc.) is byte-
identical at the call-site level; only linkage of two helpers
changed.

Spec: specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 13.6 (PR14a-g).
Reference: LS1046A Reference Manual sec 8.7.4 (scheme registers),
           sec 8.7.5 (extract record format), sec 8.4 (port ids).

Signed-off-by: Miha Kralj <miha@mihakralj.com>
